Ordered a standard burger with cheddar, onions and their two8two sauce. Asked for it well done (don't judge me) and it came back rather crispy on the edges, but that's ok because the flavor was good (I find that most places don't season their burgers, but this one def had salt & pepper at least). What I didn't like was that they only have cheddar or feta. What kind of burger joint only offers two kinds of cheese? Also, there was no lettuce or tomato on it (did I have to request that separately?) The fries were ok (reminiscent of McDonald's fries, but fresher) and onion rings were alright, nothing special. The two8two sauce was a nice addition (it's mayo, mustard, pickles, garlic and paprika), went very well on the burger and as a dipping sauce for the fries and rings. Would I go back? Maybe if they give more options than just "beef, cheddar and feta." I'd rather go to Burger Village in Park Slope.
